# ApiV2 Chart Colors

## Config file

All chart colors are defined in `ApiV2/colors.config.jsonc`.

- **Do not** use raw hex (e.g. `"#2d6a9f"`) in ApiV2 JSON files.
- **Do** use token names from the config (e.g. `"chartPcVnPrimary"`).

```json
"color": ["chartPcVnPrimary"]
```

## Changing a color

Edit the hex value once in `ApiV2/colors.config.jsonc`. All JSON files referencing that token pick up the new color.

## Adding a new color

1. Look up the name on [ArtyClick Color Name Finder](https://colors.artyclick.com/color-name-finder/).
2. Add a semantic token + hex to `colors.config.jsonc`.
3. Document usage in the comment block at the bottom of the config file.
4. Use the token in JSON — never the hex literal.

## Token naming

Use semantic names: `chartPcVnPrimary`, `chartTargetBar`, not `blue1`.

## Generators

Scripts under `scripts/` that emit ApiV2 chart JSON must output color **tokens**, not hex values.
